post_text:
HS ~ The Lady Bulldogs Varsity and Junior Varsity teams were victorious last night against Hempstead High School. The Varsity match went 4 sets, with scores of 25-20, 15-25, 25-20, 25-21.
Varsity Highlights:
Junior and Captain Sanaa Scott with 14 kills, 2 blocks, 2 saves, one ace, and one dig.
Sophomore Abigail Armacost with 4 blocks, 1 ace, 1 save, and 1 kill.
Junior Dasia Triplett with 2 digs, 1 block, 2 saves, and great sets all night.
Junior Varsity Highlights:
The Lady Bulldogs played as a team and never gave up the fight to take the win back! They won their first set, lost the second, and came together to win the third.
Great job ladies!
The Lady Bulldogs travel to East Bernard on Friday with game times of 4:30 Varsity and 5:30 JV.

HISD ~ Hitchcock ISD is pleased to announce a modification in their meal service for area children. Hitchcock ISD has been granted TDA approval to operate the Seamless Summer Option (SSO) for Breakfast and Lunch meals served for the remainder of 2020. This allows any child to pick up receive both meals each day without the need to present proof of enrollment, age, grade or specific residency. Any child 18 years or younger may receive these meals daily (M – F) from 11:30 am to 1 pm at the following locations:

Crosby Middle School
Hitchcock Primary
Stewart Elementary
Bent Oaks Apt.
Emerald Oaks Apt.
The Village Apt.
Galilee Baptist Church
Freddiesville

Starting Monday, August 17th, Hitchcock ISD has designated 3 primary meal pickup locations for any school age person to receive free meals. Those sites are Stewart Elementary, Crosby Middle School, and Hitchcock Primary We will also have a bus parked at the following locations below for meal pickup. One bus will be split between the Bent Oaks and he Life at the Emerald Oaks.

Meals will be distributed from 11:30 to 1:00, Monday through Friday. We will be passing out 3 meals per child. To receive a meal the Student/Parent must present proof of the students active enrollment at Hitchcock ISD. This proof must be presented each time a meal is picked up.

Please throw away all trash from these meals in a trash can and not on the ground.

1) The corner of Heron & Highland Dr.

2) Bent Oaks Apartments (11:30 – 12:15)

3) The Life at Emerald Oaks (12:15 – 1:00)

4) The Village Apartments

5) Galilee Missionary Baptist Church

HS ~ The Lady Bulldogs Volleyball Team took a first match loss against Anahuac. The match went 4 sets- they lost the first two, came back and won the third, and then were defeated in the fourth by 2 points.
Match highlights:
Sophomore Abigail Armacost with 2 kills, 2 blocks, and some great serves. Front row MVP.
Senior Amani Williams with 3 back row kills, several great saves, sets, and serves. All around MVP.
Junior J’Lailah Dotson with several near impossible saves, great serves, and most accurate passing. Back row MVP.
The Lady Bulldogs recognize the areas with room for growth, and will overcome them to become stronger than ever.

Good evening Bulldog athletes and Parents,

Working with Galveston County Health officials, we will begin our Fall practice for football and volleyball, tomorrow, Thursday, August 6th. UIL allowed all schools in 1A to 4A divisions to begin practice on August 3rd. We want to assure you that we will be following the COVID 19 mitigation guidelines from both UIL and local health officials.

text:

Working with Galveston County Health officials, we will begin our Fall practice for football and volleyball, tomorrow, Thursday, August 6th. UIL allowed all schools in 1A to 4A divisions to begin practice on August 3rd. We want to assure you that we will be following the COVID 19 mitigation guidelines from both UIL and local health officials.

Football practice will begin at 4pm with athletes not arriving prior to 3:30pm. Volleyball practice will begin at 3pm. Parents can come at 2pm to complete all required UIL and Health paperwork. No athlete will be able to participate until all forms are completed.

If you have any questions, please contact the Hitchcock ISD Athletic department at 409-316-6544 ext. 1227 or email csmith@hitchcockisd.org

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Galveston County, Texas
April 13 at 10:03 AM ·

The United States Census 2020 has been sent out and everyone is encouraged to fill it out if they haven’t already done so.

Getting an accurate count of people in Galveston County is extremely important. Census data will determine representation at the federal level as well as how billions of dollars will be spent across the country over the next 10 years.

For more questions about the 2020 Census and how to fill it out, visit www.2020census.gov or call 844-330-2020.

post_text: Hitchcock graduate Carrie Thiem Maxwell.
shared_text:
I am UTMB
April 2 at 2:28 PM ·

Members of our Assay Development Services Division (ADSD) have been working wonders in the Galveston National Laboratory. Led by ADSD co-director Dr. Rick Pyles, they developed the SARS-CoV-2 test system being used in the GNL, enabling UTMB to substantially increase its COVID-19 testing capabilities. Their work included validating the test in the clinical lab and working tirelessly to conduct the vast majority of COVID-19 tests that UTMB has conducted to date. By sharing the assay with other institutions, they have also allowed for more widespread testing of patients across the nation. Amazing work by Dr. Pyles, who is a professor in the Departments of Pediatrics and Microbiology & Immunology, and his team members, Aaron Miller, ASDS Assistant Director, and Carrie Maxwell, Research Associate III in Microbiology & Immunology. #WeAreUTMB

Hitchcock ISD
March 26 at 5:42 PM ·

HISD ~ On Monday, March 30th, Crosby and Stewart will be issuing students Chromebooks from 11am to 2pm. If your child does not have a device to connect to google classroom they will need to pick up a chromebook as we transition to online assignments at these 2 campuses. If you have one child who attends Crosby and one who attend Stewart you will need to visit both campuses to check out the chromebook. A parent or guardian is required to check out the device because there will be an agreement that needs to be signed.
If you do not have wifi at home you can receive 2 months for free from Xfinity through the Internet Essential plan which can be found at https://www.internetessentials.com/ or by calling 1-855-846-8376.

If you are unable to pickup a chromebook during the time above please email one of the people listed below and we will figure out a way to get the device to you.

Stewart ~ Ms. Fain ~ lfain@hitchcockisd.org
Crosby ~ Ms. Crawford ~ ccrawford1@hitchcockisd.org
Either ~ Mr. Armacost ~ carmacost@hitchcockisd.org

If your child does not have a device to connect to google classroom they will need to pick up a chromebook as we transition to online assignments at these 2 campuses. If you have one child who attends Crosby and one who attend Stewart you will need to visit both campuses to check out the chromebook. A parent or guardian is required to check out the device because there will be an agreement that needs to be signed.
If you do not have wifi at home you can receive 2 months for free from Xfinity through the Internet Essential plan which can be found at https://www.internetessentials.com/ or by calling 1-855-846-8376.

If you are unable to pickup a chromebook during the time above please email one of the people listed below and we will figure out a way to get the device to you.

Stewart ~ Ms. Fain ~ lfain@hitchcockisd.org
Crosby ~ Ms. Crawford ~ ccrawford1@hitchcockisd.org
Either ~ Mr. Armacost ~ carmacost@hitchcockisd.org

post_text:
Good Evening

It was brought to our attention that a group of people used the football stadium today without the districts permission. The gates were locked and these individuals (between 30-40 of them) climbed the fence to play football. We do have several cameras at the stadium and we will be reaching out to those individuals we identify.
Just a friendly reminder that unauthorized use of Hitchcock ISD facilities can carry a criminal trespassing charge. Currently the city is also under a stay at home ordinance which can also carry up to a 2,000 fine for violators.

***The food program will be available until school resumes. Please continue to help us spread the word so no student goes without a meal. We handed out a total of 4,121 meals last week. Special thanks to the food service and transportation department for making this possible each day.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Hitchcock ISD has designated 8 meal pickup locations for any school age person to receive free meals. We will have a bus parked at the following locations for meal pickup from 10:30am to 11:30am for lunch and again at 2:30pm to 3:30pm for a second meal. This will occur Monday through Friday.
***Remember your child has to be with you to receive the meal. If you are out driving and see the bus please feel free to stop at any site listed below.

1) KFHS parking lot
2) Crosby Middle School – you will pick up from the cafeteria
3) Bent Oaks Apartments
4) The Life at Emerald Oaks Apartments
5) The Village Apartments
6) Galilee Missionary Baptist Church
7) Joe Moore Park
8) The corner of Heron & Highland Dr. (Freddiesville)

From our Superintendent:

In order to help prevent the broader spread of COVID-19, Hitchcock ISD and all school districts in Galveston County will be closed next week, March 16-20. All school activities/events are also canceled effective immediately.

Maintenance, Transportation, Technology, and Custodial Staff will report for duty at 8:00 on Monday- March 16.

A plan is being finalized for the distribution of meals and will be communicated once finalized.

I will be closely monitoring this situation and will report any updates as decisions are made.

HS ~ Countee earns top honor among Hitchcock girls basketball all-district winners.

The undefeated district champion Hitchcock Lady Bulldogs were heavily awarded in 24-3A's postseason all-district honors.

Headlining the Hitchcock representatives were district most valuable player sophomore Chloe Countee, offensive player of the year senior Demi Dickey and coach of the year Dante McDaniel.

Earning all-district first-team honors were sophomore Sanaa Scott and senior Chrishauna McDaniel. Named to the second team from the Lady Bulldogs were junior Tra'Kemmia Elam and freshman Abigail Armacost. Receiving honorable mentions were Breanna Birdow and Jimile Johnson.

post_text:
HS~ From coach Caliz:
Lady Bulldogs Fastpitch fought for a great win vs Anahuac this evening. Playing a very close game and pushing through to the end with a score of 5-4. Dasia Triplett pitched the entire 7 innings, with 8 strikeouts and managing to get her team out of the inning twice with bases loaded. Chloe Countee also stepped up and made 7 outs on her own, with the assistance of our 1st baseman Emily Ramos. The bats came alive in the later part of the game to take us home with a win. Super Proud of our Lady Bulldogs!!!

KFHS ~ Hitchcock Independent School District “KIDS FIRST” Head Start will begin accepting applications for the 2020 - 2021 school year. Registration dates are as follows:
March 25, 2020 to June 18, 2020 and July 6, 2020 through the remainder of the school year.

Applications will be accepted in the Head Start office located at 5701 FM 2004, Hitchcock, Texas, from 9:00 AM – 11:30 AM and 1:00 PM – 2:30 PM. Students who are currently enrolled and intend to return for the 2020-2021 school year are also requested to register on these dates.

Eligibility requirements: Child must be three or four years old by September 1, 2020 and must meet income eligibility guidelines and/or qualify for free or reduced National Nutrition Program.

For additional information, please call Kahne Girouard, Family Service Coordinator, or Shirley Alexander, Family Service Assistant at 409-316-6541.
text:
KFHS ~ Hitchcock Independent School District “KIDS FIRST” Head Start will begin accepting applications for the 2020 - 2021 school year. Registration dates are as follows:
March 25, 2020 to June 18, 2020 and July 6, 2020 through the remainder of the school year.

Applications will be accepted in the Head Start office located at 5701 FM 2004, Hitchcock, Texas, from 9:00 AM – 11:30 AM and 1:00 PM – 2:30 PM. Students who are currently enrolled and intend to return for the 2020-2021 school year are also requested to register on these dates.

Eligibility requirements: Child must be three or four years old by September 1, 2020 and must meet income eligibility guidelines and/or qualify for free or reduced National Nutrition Program.

For additional information, please call Kahne Girouard, Family Service Coordinator, or Shirley Alexander, Family Service Assistant at 409-316-6541.

HPS ~ Students of the Week

Melina Guzman in Ms. Sharp’s 2nd grade class helped a student in class that was at the nurse close to dismissal time by getting his backpack and supper ready for him for when he returned.

Michael Cox in Ms. Turner’s Kindergarten class(not pictured) helped a student that was scared to cross a section of the playground. Michael waited for the student to cross, and even held the steps still so that the other student was safe. Michael is a hard worker in the classroom, and he is always considerate and polite to other students.

Amelia Rodriguez in Ms. Turner’s Kindergarten class heard a student calling out for help at a station that he was unfamiliar with. Amelia left her station on the other side of the room and showed him how the station worked. Amelia always works hard and often asks to help other students. She truly wants other students to be successful and is a great friend to everyone in the classroom.

HPS ~ Students of the Week
Ronnie Bryant in Ms. Cooper’s kindergarten class always tries his best to make sure everyone is happy. If anyone is upset or having a bad day, he always wants to know how to make it better. He also protected one of his classmates from being kicked by another student by sitting in between them. Good job Ronnie.

Grayson Byrd in Ms. Lehnert’s 1st grade class saw a staff member injured in PE . Coach Caldwell asked Grayson to get the nurse and he sprang into action. He went and got the nurse and she asked him to go get the wheelchair. He once again went on a mission to get the wheelchair and deliver it to the gym. His quick action and caring heart show what great character Grayson has. Way to go Grayson!

Mirah Tucker in Ms. Austin’s kindergarten class was overheard by her teacher explaining to some of her friends how to make good choices during school. She even complimented some friends that she noticed making some of these good choices.

HPS ~ Aaliyah Maupin in Ms. Dean’s 1st grade class saw a friend in another class fall at recess and she stopped swinging, ran up to him, helped him up, brushed off the mulch and dirt, and asked him if he was okay! It was so kind and thoughtful! Awesome job being a great friend!

Kyla Preston in Ms. Valdez’s 1st grade class saw a friend sitting at a table by herself, Kyla offered to move with her so she wouldn’t be alone. When a friend was upset and crying, she gave her a big bear hug and told her everything was going to be OK. Kyla is always showing empathy to other students and is always willing to help out when the teacher needs help. She makes good choices and is always willing to help a friend in need.

HS ~ The High School will be hosting a District and Community-wide Blood Drive, on Tuesday, January 7th, from 8am-3pm. We are inviting all members of our schools and community to donate tomorrow.

This time, all those that successfully give will receive a "Hoodie Sweat Shirt" to show our appreciation for your donation. Faculty and community may go straight from the parking lot to the donation buses parked in front of Hitchcock High School. You will receive priority over our students that are on campus.

January is always a time of the year when our Blood Banks become low. We need YOU to please help build that supply up again. Thanking you in advance, and see you on Tuesday.

HPS ~ Trinity Martinez in Ms. Turner’s Kindergarten class cleaned up water in the hallway without being asked. She had gone to the restroom and saw water spilled in the hallway. She got paper towels and cleaned it up, not realizing that another teacher had seen her act of kindness. She is always finding other friends to help, and she is a super student. She is a rock star!

Marc Munoz in Ms. Perkins Second Grade class goes above and beyond when he sees someone that doesn't understand he helps them by trying to explain things. I watch him work in stations as a leader in his group. He shows kindness while others do not help. I am very proud of him overcoming his own obstacles in class and then using his experiences of struggles to help others become successful. Way to go Marc!

HISD ~ Today the parent portal formally known as TxConnect will change to a new version called Ascender Parent Portal. Your current user name and password will work with the new site so there is no need to do anything extra. If you have the old URL saved to your computer please visit our website and click on the Parent Portal link to save the new URL.
If you have any problems please let us know.

HS ~ The football team will honor Veterans before the upcoming home game (11/08/19). If you are a Veteran and would like to participate please meet at the track entrance on the home side at 7:00pm. The game starts at 7:30pm.
